  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The magnetic properties of zigzag metallic chains have been calculated based on the Monte Carlo simulation. The reduced transition temperatures and the magnetization have been obtained for different exchange interactions and for different crystal fields. The hysteresis cycle is obtained for different exchange interactions, temperatures and crystal field. The superparamagnetic behavior is obtained for a specific value of temperatures and crystal field. The second-order phase transitions are also observed. The obtained results are comparable with some given by experiment results and theoretical calculations.</subfield>
